#
# Pointing calibrator list PCALS4.7 for the GBT - June 2013
#
# J.Condon wrote:
# updated the GBT pointing calibrator list by adding 30, 44, 70, 
# and 100 GHz flux densities from the final Planck Catalogue of Compact 
# Sources (Planck Collaboration, 2013, A&A, in press) and 20 GHz fluxes 
# from Righini, S., Carretti, E., Ricci, R. et al. 2012 MNRAS, 426, 2107 
# "A 20 GHz bright sample for delta > +72 deg: I. Catalogue".  
# This should significantly refresh the high-frequency flux densities, 
# many of which are variable.  The new GBT pointing calibrator list is 
# called PCALS4.7 and is available from ftp://ftp.cv.nrao.edu/NRAO-staff/jcondon/  
#
# Pointing calibrator list PCALS4.5 for the GBT - December 2011
# Data from WMAP7, ATCA, and Planck has been added.
# See PTCS project note 72.0 for details.
#
# BMIN and BMAX are the minimum and maximum beam sizes (arcseconds)
#   for which the source is suitable.
# S20, S6, ... are in Janskys

# PF-band (0.6 GHz or 50cm)
# S50 is in Janskys; OFFSET field is from ra,dec=0,0
# sources stronger than 0.2 JY at 0.60 GHz

# CALFIND: Warning! Large GBT beam; use only strong    
#          calibrators to minimize confusion
#          (rms = 0.119 Jy/beam at this frequency).

FORMAT=SPHERICAL
COORDMODE=J2000

HEAD = NAME      RA           DEC            S50  OFFSET Gold
